OL,3,CWhat happened in the Morecambe Bay
OL,4,Ccockle picking disaster?
OL,6,FMany were from a farming background,
OL,7,Fand had never even seen the sea until
OL,8,Fthey went cockle picking.
OL,10,FYet even after their deaths, the
OL,11,Ffamilies had to continue paying
OL,12,Fthousands of pounds to the people who
OL,13,Fbrought them into the country.
OL,15,FThe tragedy led to new laws to protect
OL,16,Ftrafficked workers, contributed to the
OL,17,Fintroduction of the Modern Slavery
OL,18,FAct, and encouraged stronger
OL,19,Fguidelines around those working in
OL,20,Fcockle picking.
