OL,6,FHe added: "it was something no one had
OL,7,Fcome across so in reality it's one of
OL,8,Fthose things that generates memories
OL,9,Fand we have to live with them."
OL,11,FAt 10:46pm that evening, Tony Eden Jr,
OL,12,Fa local businessman, called the
OL,13,Fcoastguard to tell them he and his
OL,14,Ffather had employed the cockle pickers.
OL,16,FA member of the RNLI recalls the
OL,17,Fmoment he came across the bodies of
OL,18,Fthe cockle pickers.
