OL,3,CWhat happened in the Morecambe Bay
OL,4,Ccockle picking disaster?
OL,6,FHowever, the crime gangs incurred
OL,7,Fheavy debts on the workers for
OL,8,Ftrafficking them. Most of their
OL,9,Fearnings went towards paying off this
OL,10,Fdebt.
OL,12,FWhile working for the crime gangs,
OL,13,Fthey were also forced to pay for
OL,14,Faccommodation where up to 30 people
OL,15,Fwould share a single toilet.
OL,17,FOf the 23 victims, two were women,
OL,18,Fwith the rest mainly men in their 20s
OL,19,Fand 30s. Two were over 40, and one
OL,20,Fmale was under 20.
